246
00:14:07,900 --> 00:14:09,430
Two servings of the usual.

247
00:14:09,430 --> 00:14:10,370
Got it.

248
00:14:11,160 --> 00:14:14,450
Is this the restaurant you usually go to?

249
00:14:14,800 --> 00:14:18,020
It has a very traditional
and historic feel to it.

250
00:14:18,600 --> 00:14:20,050
Here you go. Thank you for waiting.

251
00:14:20,380 --> 00:14:23,130
The Hijikata Special, otherwise
known as Dog Food.

252
00:14:23,650 --> 00:14:26,840
Is there anyone who wouldn't be
disgusted by the sight of that?

253
00:14:27,540 --> 00:14:29,020
Disgusted?

254
00:14:29,360 --> 00:14:32,180
I get a sour taste in my mouth
just looking at that.

255
00:14:32,490 --> 00:14:34,520
What is this?

256
00:14:35,500 --> 00:14:36,550
It's lunch!!

257
00:14:46,550 --> 00:14:48,420
The One Piece of flavors is in my mouth!!

258
00:14:48,420 --> 00:14:50,350
It's the Trichiliocosm of flavor!!

259
00:14:53,670 --> 00:14:56,060
Do you really think it's delicious?

260
00:14:56,830 --> 00:14:59,260
Yes. It's very delicious.

261
00:15:00,010 --> 00:15:01,600
I've found a kindred spirit here of all places.

262
00:15:01,600 --> 00:15:04,940
Why do you ask that?

263
00:15:05,740 --> 00:15:07,310
No... It's nothing.

264
00:15:08,960 --> 00:15:12,650
This is bad! Hijikata-san was
a little pleased about that!

265
00:15:12,650 --> 00:15:14,770
He looks happy he's met
a fellow mayo lover.

266
00:15:15,010 --> 00:15:16,900
He's gone for wool, but
came back shorn.

267
00:15:16,900 --> 00:15:19,930
Thank you for introducing me
to something so delicious.

268
00:15:23,410 --> 00:15:25,910
Come on, Gin-san, Kagura-chan, hurry.

269
00:15:26,340 --> 00:15:28,160
They look like they're hitting
it off pretty well.

270
00:15:28,160 --> 00:15:30,380
We should let them get together.
Combine okay?

271
00:15:28,160 --> 00:15:30,380
[Note: Parody of the anime, Chōdenji
Robo Combattler V.]

272
00:15:30,990 --> 00:15:33,950
If anything, they're a nice couple.

273
00:15:34,160 --> 00:15:35,860
You're suddenly giving up?!

274
00:15:36,770 --> 00:15:38,700
Hijikata-san keeps looking at us!

275
00:15:39,080 --> 00:15:42,080
He looks like he thinks everyone
in the world is a liar!

276
00:15:42,530 --> 00:15:45,810
Oh well. Shall we try the next plan?

277
00:15:49,550 --> 00:15:51,510
Hey, there! Things are getting
pretty passionate here.

278
00:15:51,510 --> 00:15:53,840
You've been showing off quite a bit!!

279
00:15:54,380 --> 00:15:57,210
Don't act so cool just because
you've got a woman.

280
00:15:57,530 --> 00:16:00,280
How dare you prance around
and flirt like that.

281
00:16:00,280 --> 00:16:02,390
We'll kill you, damn it!!

282
00:16:03,450 --> 00:16:04,530
Mayo-sama.

283
00:16:06,240 --> 00:16:08,750
I-I'm sorry!!

284
00:16:10,610 --> 00:16:13,630
I apologize if I've offended you.

285
00:16:13,630 --> 00:16:18,670
U-Umm, money, right? H-Here.
Please take this and spare us.

286
00:16:19,010 --> 00:16:22,430
At least spare our lives!!

287
00:16:22,860 --> 00:16:26,100
I'll do anything. I'll even lick
the soles of your shoes!!

288
00:16:26,100 --> 00:16:28,180
What an obedient kid.

289
00:16:28,180 --> 00:16:29,370
Come on, hand it over!!

290
00:16:29,820 --> 00:16:33,740
Lick the sole of my shoes?!
Go ahead and lick them!!

291
00:16:33,740 --> 00:16:37,070
[Note: A Suica is a smart card used
to pay for train rides in Japan.]

292
00:16:33,740 --> 00:16:37,070
What's this?! There's only
3,000 yen and a Suica.

293
00:16:37,420 --> 00:16:38,930
You bastard!!

294
00:16:39,440 --> 00:16:41,910
You're an adult and you only have
3,000 yen? You must be kidding!!

295
00:16:41,910 --> 00:16:43,890
You've got more, don't you?!

296
00:16:44,330 --> 00:16:46,380
Don't hide it!!

297
00:16:46,380 --> 00:16:47,510
Jeez.

298
00:16:47,510 --> 00:16:50,450
How dare you always
use such showy lines!

299
00:16:50,980 --> 00:16:53,770
How many DVD covers
have you been on?!

300
00:16:50,980 --> 00:16:53,770
[Note: Hijikata adorns many GinTama DVD covers.]

301
00:16:54,140 --> 00:16:56,410
Don't try to act stylish, damn it!!

302
00:16:56,410 --> 00:17:02,010
[Note: Hijikata’s consumer goods have
more selection than Shinpachi’s.]

303
00:16:56,410 --> 00:17:02,010
How dare your merchandise
sell more than mine?!

304
00:16:58,570 --> 00:17:00,830
Who cares if you're the Shinsengumi's
Vice-Chief?!

305
00:17:03,740 --> 00:17:05,320
All of you, cut it out!!

306
00:17:05,600 --> 00:17:07,920
You're taking too long! How
long do you plan on doing this?!

307
00:17:07,920 --> 00:17:09,560
Anyway, you're just talking
about me, aren't you?!

308
00:17:09,560 --> 00:17:11,040
You're talking about my
normal self, aren't you?!

309
00:17:11,040 --> 00:17:13,200
Why are you using this moment

310
00:17:13,200 --> 00:17:15,010
to vent your pent-up anger?!

311
00:17:15,010 --> 00:17:17,200
You bastard!

312
00:17:21,620 --> 00:17:26,680
Mayo-sama, you risked your
life to protect me, didn't you?

313
00:17:27,070 --> 00:17:31,940
Huh? Well, umm, uhh… It was a
conditioned reflex or something.

314
00:17:31,940 --> 00:17:34,700
You're getting bashful. That's so cute.

315
00:17:35,670 --> 00:17:39,380
How could I say something
so embarrassing?

316
00:17:40,340 --> 00:17:41,750
Don't hate me…

317
00:17:41,750 --> 00:17:46,090
for saying that.

318
00:17:46,400 --> 00:17:48,160
I don't care what happens anymore.

319
00:17:48,160 --> 00:17:49,110
I'm running away.

320
00:17:49,280 --> 00:17:50,790
Running away, Hijikata-san?

321
00:17:51,110 --> 00:17:55,070
And leave that girl permanently scarred?

322
00:17:55,620 --> 00:17:57,460
It doesn't matter how many men you kill.

323
00:17:57,460 --> 00:18:01,340
You must never betray
a girl's pure feelings.

324
00:18:01,790 --> 00:18:04,610
Whoa! He's saying obnoxious
things again!

325
00:18:05,320 --> 00:18:07,260
Kagura-chan, do you have
any suggestions?

326
00:18:07,260 --> 00:18:11,530
If he runs away, she'll just forget
him after three days.

327
00:18:12,060 --> 00:18:15,130
She's got a harsh and really
plausible opinion.

328
00:18:15,440 --> 00:18:19,690
Aww, crap! Why did this
have to happen to me?

329
00:18:20,920 --> 00:18:22,410
Running away is fine,

330
00:18:22,410 --> 00:18:25,850
but are you prepared to never
appear in front of her again?

331
00:18:26,240 --> 00:18:27,220
Of course.

332
00:18:27,810 --> 00:18:30,560
Are you prepared to do
anything to run away?

333
00:18:30,560 --> 00:18:34,010
It depends on the situation.
I'll do whatever I can!

334
00:18:35,180 --> 00:18:36,610
You're serious, right?

335
00:18:36,610 --> 00:18:37,660
Yeah.

336
00:18:38,260 --> 00:18:40,810
Mayo-sama? Mayo-sama!

337
00:18:41,150 --> 00:18:42,940
Where have you gone?

338
00:18:43,510 --> 00:18:45,070
Mayo-sama!

339
00:18:45,120 --> 00:18:47,000
Listen to me and don't turn around.

340
00:18:47,000 --> 00:18:47,410
Mayo-sa—

341
00:18:47,410 --> 00:18:48,630
Don't turn around!

342
00:18:51,610 --> 00:18:54,100
There’s something I haven't told you.

343
00:18:55,000 --> 00:18:56,530
What is it?

344
00:18:57,210 --> 00:18:58,620
I'm actually…

345
00:18:59,180 --> 00:19:01,240
The Prince of the Planet
Mayo Maniac, mayo.

346
00:19:02,390 --> 00:19:03,880
A prince?!

347
00:19:03,880 --> 00:19:06,020
You can turn around now, mayo.

348
00:19:15,720 --> 00:19:19,820
It's useless. There's no way
this is going to work.

349
00:19:19,820 --> 00:19:21,930
I thought so.

350
00:19:22,710 --> 00:19:28,190
I sensed that you were
not a normal person.

351
00:19:28,190 --> 00:19:31,340
It worked!! I've added “mayo” to the
end of my sentences and it worked!!

352
00:19:31,710 --> 00:19:34,890
I'll die if I stay on Earth too long, mayo.

353
00:19:36,020 --> 00:19:38,230
It seems I'm at my limit, mayo.

354
00:19:39,640 --> 00:19:41,410
Are you going?

355
00:19:42,140 --> 00:19:44,360
I'm going to be picked up shortly, mayo.

356
00:19:46,060 --> 00:19:47,500
Take me with you.

357
00:19:48,520 --> 00:19:51,870
I don't mind eating mayonnaise
for every meal.

358
00:19:52,550 --> 00:19:54,320
I-I…

359
00:19:55,310 --> 00:19:56,520
Please.

360
00:19:56,830 --> 00:19:58,640
I want to go with you.

361
00:19:59,800 --> 00:20:02,020
This is headed in the wrong
direction, isn't it?

362
00:20:02,020 --> 00:20:05,010
No, hold on, Toshiro!! You can do this.

363
00:20:06,470 --> 00:20:09,910
D-Don't be silly.

364
00:20:09,910 --> 00:20:14,000
Planet Mayo Maniac is a remote planet covered
in a mayonnaise atmosphere, mayo.

365
00:20:14,330 --> 00:20:17,270
You wouldn't be able to
survive there, mayo.

366
00:20:17,270 --> 00:20:20,800
It's best if you live on Earth, mayo.

367
00:20:21,520 --> 00:20:24,070
I'll always be watching over you, mayo.

368
00:20:26,030 --> 00:20:27,710
Always?

369
00:20:28,640 --> 00:20:29,690
Y-Yeah, mayo!

370
00:20:31,280 --> 00:20:32,380
What's wrong, mayo?

371
00:20:42,140 --> 00:20:44,650
Even though this is goodbye.

372
00:20:46,460 --> 00:20:48,710
I won't cry.

373
00:20:55,300 --> 00:20:57,690
Prince, it's time, mayo.

374
00:20:57,690 --> 00:20:59,420
We've come for you, mayo.

375
00:21:01,550 --> 00:21:03,340
Live happily, mayo!

376
00:21:03,940 --> 00:21:04,990
Mayo-sama…

377
00:21:04,990 --> 00:21:06,510
We're leaving, mayo.

378
00:21:06,510 --> 00:21:07,790
Mayo!

379
00:21:09,320 --> 00:21:10,210
Mayo-sama…

380
00:21:12,990 --> 00:21:14,150
Mayo-sama!

381
00:21:14,750 --> 00:21:16,970
Farewell!

382
00:21:18,520 --> 00:21:19,330
Farewell, mayo…

383
00:21:19,940 --> 00:21:22,200
Farewell, mayo…

384
00:21:23,620 --> 00:21:28,090
Mayo-sama… I'm sure
that we'll meet again.

385
00:21:32,190 --> 00:21:34,580
Kuriko-san is a pretty nice girl.

386
00:21:34,580 --> 00:21:35,900
Yeah…

387
00:21:36,440 --> 00:21:38,250
What's wrong, prince?

388
00:21:39,820 --> 00:21:41,350
Did you fall in love with…

389
00:21:41,350 --> 00:21:43,580
You idiot, it's not like that!!

390
00:21:56,790 --> 00:21:58,790
That's my story, mayo.

391
00:21:59,750 --> 00:22:02,260
You're really annoying, mayo.

